<p>A proofreading and writing consultancy developed by a pair of philosophers is offering a set of modest scholarships for graduate students with dyslexia. <span id="more-55357"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-55358 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dyslexia-dictionary-2-1024x776.png" alt="" width="600" height="455" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dyslexia-dictionary-2-1024x776.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dyslexia-dictionary-2-300x227.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dyslexia-dictionary-2-768x582.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dyslexia-dictionary-2-1536x1164.png 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dyslexia-dictionary-2-400x303.png 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/dyslexia-dictionary-2.png 1712w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p>The scholarships are offered by <a href="https://www.lexacademic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lex Academic</a>, run by Louise Chapman and Constantine Sandis, and have been announced recently to coincide with <a href="https://dyslexiaida.org/october-is-dyslexia-awareness-month-2/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dyslexia Awareness Month</a>.</p>
<p>They are offering one scholarship in each of three disciplines: philosophy, classics, and art history. The scholarship includes Â£500 (approximately $671) for each winner and free proofreading services from Lex Academic for their doctoral thesis.</p>
<p>You can learn more about the scholarships <a href="https://www.lexacademic.com/scholarships/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
